Conclusions. In line with Maher and Spitzer it is suggested that increased automatic spreading activation underlies schizophrenia-typical language disturbances which in our study cannot be attributed to confounding variables such as diﬀerent reaction time baselines, medication or length of illness. Finally, results conﬁrm that the psychometric high-risk approach is an important tool for investigating issues relevant to schizophrenia.},
