Conclusions. These results suggest that many of the brain regions involved in emotional face perception, including the amygdala, are equally recruited in both schizophrenia and controls, but ﬂat aﬀect can also moderate activity in some other brain regions, notably in the left amygdala and parahippocampal gyrus bilaterally. There were no signiﬁcant group diﬀerences in the volume of the amygdala.},
